title: Google\Cloud\Eventarc\V1\Channel
name: Channel
description:
A representation of the Channel resource.

A Channel is a resource on which event providers publish their events. The published events are delivered through the transport associated with the channel. Note that a channel is associated with exactly one event provider.

Generated from protobuf message google.cloud.eventarc.v1.Channel

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.name
params.description: Required. The resource name of the channel. Must be unique within the location on the project and must be in projects/{project}/locations/{location}/channels/{channel_id} format.

params.name: data.uid
params.description: Output only. Server assigned unique identifier for the channel. The value is a UUID4 string and guaranteed to remain unchanged until the resource is deleted.

params.name: data.provider
params.description: Required. The name of the event provider (e.g. Eventarc SaaS partner) associated with the channel. This provider will be granted permissions to publish events to the channel. Format: projects/{project}/locations/{location}/providers/{provider_id}.

params.name: data.pubsub_topic
params.description: Output only. The name of the Pub/Sub topic created and managed by Eventarc system as a transport for the event delivery. Format: projects/{project}/topics/{topic_id}.

params.name: data.state
params.description: Output only. The state of a Channel.

params.name: data.activation_token
params.description: Output only. The activation token for the channel. The token must be used by the provider to register the channel for publishing.
